    <text>
        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>New York<lb/>
                Feb&#39;y 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr Morais&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mother desires<lb/> me to express to you how <hi rend="underline">very</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">much</hi> she regretted not being<lb/> at home&#44; when you so kindly<lb/> took the trouble to come so far<lb/> from your usual resting place<lb/> to see her.<lb/></p>
            <p>Her young grand&#45;daughter was<lb/> suffering greatly on Sunday with<lb/> quinsey sore throat and we<lb/> were so anxious about her&#44; that<lb/> as soon as possible after<lb/> breakfast&#44; Mama went to her<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to find&#44; thank God&#44; that the<lb/> fever had broken &#38; recovery<lb/> begun&#44; the greatest possible relief<lb/> to all of us.<lb/></p>
            <p>We hope that you will not<lb/> permit this disappointment <del>from</del><lb/> to deter you from coming to us&#44;<lb/> whenever in the future you may<lb/> have a spare hour in our city&#44;<lb/> and&#44; as our own disappointment<lb/> is greater than yours can possibly<lb/> be&#44; please let us know the day<lb/> before&#44; that <hi rend="underline">neither</hi> of us may miss<lb/> the privilege of welcoming you&#44; for<lb/> although my dear mother rarely leaves<lb/> home now&#44; save on a very sunny<lb/> afternoon&#44; when I am able to<lb/> persuade her to take a short<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>walk&#44; my own duties sometimes<lb/> require my absence from home.<lb/>  I wish indeed you could have<lb/> talked with dear Mama.  She<lb/> bears her great sorrow with a<lb/> submission &#38; resignation to the will<lb/> of the most High that is an example<lb/> to all her children.<lb/></p>
            <p>We both thank you &#38; your dear<lb/> Daughters for heartfelt words of<lb/> sympathy &#38; I deeply appreciate<lb/> your having thought of me.<lb/></p>
            <p>One trembles to think how near<lb/> in our lives sorrow is to joy.<lb/>
                With kindest regards&#44; in which my<lb/> dear mother &#38; Brother unite&#44;<lb/> 
                Believe me yours sincerely<lb/>
                &#38; affectionately&#44;<lb/>
                Nina Samuel<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
